4 CONC nd came to
Americn 46 years ago, living in Martins
Ferry for a short time before
coming to Youngstown.
Mr. &lt;span class=&quot;highlight-text&quot;&gt;Kascher&lt;/span&gt; made his home on
Ridge Ave.
4 CONC  with Mra. Mary Ongyerth.
Ho was a former night watchman in
the Hartzell Brothers stors but had
been retired for the past five years.
He was a member of the Honterus
Lutheran Church.
Mr. &lt;span clas
4 CONC s=&quot;highlight-text&quot;&gt;Kascher&lt;/span&gt; s wife, the former
