1 NOTE <p>Lithuanian Birth Record:</p><p><p>EG, Khana Sara</p></p><p><p>Shimel Leib, Iosel Itsyk, Eta</p></p><p><p>29/9/1882 28 Tishri</p></p><p><p>Telsiai Telsiai Kaunas</p></p><p><p>Town-dweller</p></p><p>
2 CONC <p>Family from Plunge</p></p><p><p>Telsiai 1882</p></p><p><p>F52 	2268931 / 2  LVIA/1226/1/1315</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>Death Record:</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>Telsiai	1887	19F	EG</p></p><p><p>Kha
2 CONC na Sora	Shimel Leib</p></p><p><p>scarlatina	5	16	6	1887	6 Tamuz	Telsiai	Telsiai	Kaunas		Plunge		Belongs to Plunge JC	LVIA/1226/1/2071</p><p><p></p></p><p><p>10/2011</p></p><p><p>I have the sad duty to
2 CONC  inform you that I found another Telz vital record.  Khana Sarah Aug, eldest daughter of Shimon Leib and Etta (Ganz) Aug-Levine died at the age of 5 years on June 16, 1887 corresponding to the Hebrew 
2 CONC date 6 Tammuz.  She died of Scarlet Fever in the city of Telz, though the record indicates her family was registered in Plunge.</p><p><p></p></p><p><p>This record proves that Berny had another aunt, a
2 CONC n older sister to his father Isadore.</p><p></p>
