1 NOTE Believe he was the son of Gottried Schwartz's second wife, Carolina Sternberg, and her first husband whose last name was Schlack or Schlank. Herman assumed the Schwartz name after his mother married G
2 CONC ottfried. <p></p> <p>The original record book at the Ev. Lutheran Immanuel Church in Meriden, CT,  shows his name for both his marriage and the birth of first child as Hermon Schwartz (Schlack). That 
2 CONC book also shows his birthplace as Neugut but an old map of the area shows the spelling as Neuguth. <p></p> <p>Cause of death - stroke. See Item #387, Page 371, of original record book at Ev. Lutheran 
2 CONC Immanuel Church, Meriden, CT. Death Certificate says Cerebral Hemorrhage - Duration four hours. <p></p> <p>At the time of his death, he was a Mechanic.</p> <p></p> <p>The year of his birth on his Deat
2 CONC h Certificate is incorrect. It shows 1849 and should be 1870. His Mother was born in 1846. <p></p> <p>He arrived on April 28, 1873 in New York aboard the S.S. Wisconsin which sailed from Liverpool and
2 CONC  Queenstown with his Mother, Gottfried Schwartz and twin half-sisters, Carline and Wilhelmine Schwartz.
