1 NOTE A lot of times known as Lena and, at least once on the 1880 Census, as Alenie. <p></p> <p>According to her Death Certificate, with information provided by her sister, Mrs. Joseph A. Cameron (Ottille a
2 CONC ka Tillie), her usual occupation was Housekeeper in a private home. She lived at 94 Columbus Avenue. <p></p> <p>Cause of Death was Arteriosclerotic heart disease with decompensation which she had for 
2 CONC four years. She also had generalized arteriosclerosis and duodenal ulcer, gall stones. She had an operation on her stomach in April 1953. <p></p> <p>She arrived on April 28, 1873 in New York aboard th
2 CONC e S.S. Wisconsin which sailed from Liverpool and Queenstown.
