Rabbi Mendel Schneerson, who was the third Rebbe of Chabad.

He was born in 1808. 
2 CONC He was the second son of the Tzemach Tzedek, his great-grandfather, Rabbi Shneur Zalman of Liadi, the founder of Chabad Hasidism, and the owner of the Tanya was his godfather. From his childhood, he c
2 CONC alled his grandfather, Rabbi Dov Ber Schneerson (known as the "middle Rebbe"), and he studied with him, and his grandfather liked him very much, used to wait for him to recite Chassidut and would call
2 CONC  him "My Stender" Says storks.
