1 NOTE <p>Rabbi Pinhas HOROWITZ (d. 3.11.1653 Prague) Married Lift Loew, the youngest daughter of Rabbi Bezalel Charif, ABD of Cologne, Germany; the son of the Maharal of Prague. They had no children. Rabbi 
2 CONC Pinhas remarried.</p><p><p></p></p><p><p>5414/1653</p></p><p><p>Harav Pinchas Horowitz, ztŌĆØl, Rav of Fulda and Dayan of Prague</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>Harav Pinchas Halevi Horowitz was a talmid o
2 CONC f Harav Yehoshua Hakohen Falk, the mechaber of the Sma.</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>His first post was as Rav and Dayan in Prague; then he served as Rav in Fulda, returning later to Prague where he liv
2 CONC ed for the rest of his life.</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>Rav Pinchas also headed a yeshivah, where he taught many talmidim. Among them was Harav Yosef Shamash from Wermaiza (Worms), who related that hi
2 CONC s rebbi said the Sma told him the following:</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>Following the churban of the first Beis Hamikdash, many Yidden settled in Wermaiza. After 70 years, when many Yidden began to re
2 CONC turn to Eretz Yisrael, they asked the golim of Wermaiza to return as well. The people who had settled there answered, ŌĆ£You can live in your Yerushalayim, the big city, while we will stay here in our
2 CONC  small Yerushalayim.ŌĆØ This was the reason, said the Sma, that the inhabitants of the city of Wermaiza were subject to so much pain and tribulation over the centuries.</p><p><p></p></p><p><p>Harav Pi
2 CONC nchas was niftar on 13 Cheshvan, 5414/1653.</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p></p></p><p>ūøū¬ūĢūæūĢū¬ ū×ūæūÖū¬ ūöūóū£ū×ūÖū¤ ūöūÖūöūĢūōūÖ ūöūóū¬ūÖū¦ ūæūżū©ūÉūÆ- ūÉūĢūśūĢ ū×ūĢū£ūĀū®- ū×ūĪūżū© 216 ūóū×ūĢūō 327-
