as seen 9/19/20

Anna Katarina Hoffman (b. 14 Oct 1664), daughter of Hans Jost Hoffman and Christina Frank. On May 6, 1726, "Anna Catherina Brecht, widow of Joh
4 CONC annes" (Johann, 1662-1719, winemaker, grape-grower, drinking establishment owner) with her two sons Stefan and Johann (Michael) petitioned to be allowed to emigrate to America. They landed in Philadel
4 CONC phia, settling first in the Germantown Section, but were in Heidelberg Twp, Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, before April 1728, when Michael was married. Johannes, Susanna, and her husband, Gabriel Roe
4 CONC scher, and Stefan's oldest two sons followed in 1731.

Johannes Michael Brecht, born 12 Oct 1662 in Neudorf and died 11 Aug 1719 in Schriesheim. He married on 29 Jul 1684 Anna Katarina Hoffman (b. 14 
4 CONC Oct 1664), daughter of Hans Jost Hoffman and Christina Frank.

Children of Catharina and Johannes Michael Brecht

1. Anna Margaretha Brecht (17 Jun 1685) married 1715 Caspar Durst
2. Appolonia Brecht 
4 CONC (9 Mar 1686)
3. Anna Elizabeth Brecht (27 May 1688) may have died 1707
4. Balthasar Brecht (26 Feb 1691 - Oct 1703)
5. Johann Stefan Brecht (17 Feb 1693 -24 Sep 1747) of whom later
6. Susanna Margaret
4 CONC he Brecht (12 Jun 1695) married 1723 Gabriel Roescher; emigrated 1731
7. Johannes Brecht (17 May 1699 - Feb 1756); married Anna Margaretha Roemer; emigrated 1731  . . . and lived in Bucks County, Penn
4 CONC sylvania
8. Anna Katharina Brecht (22 Mar 1702 - 24 Jul 1790) m. 1727 John DeHuff (d. 1751) who . . . are buried at the Moravian Church in Lancaster, Pennsylvania
9. Johann Michael Brecht (28 May 1706
4 CONC -13 Sep 1794) m. Apr 1728 Margareta Simone (1708-1778); they had 10 children in Berks County, Pennsylvania
10. Janet Brecht (1713) ???

