4 CONC &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Additional information: &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;LifeSketch: Johann Michael Brecht (called Bright after he arrived in America) was born 28 May 1706 in Schriesheim, Rhein-Neckar-Kreis, 
4 CONC Baden-W├╝rttemberg, Germany, to Anna Katherina Hoffmann and Johann Michael Brecht, keeper of a tavern and the owner of vineyards. Anna Katherina, the widow of Johannes, petitioned 6 May 1726, with her
4 CONC  two sons Stefan and Johann Michael, to be allowed to depart for America. They landed in Philadelphia on the Britannia and were in Heidelberg Township, Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, before April 172
4 CONC 8, when Michael married. Other family members came to America to join them in 1731. Michael met his future wife, Marguerita Simone/Simon, also shown as Margareta, Marguerite, and Margaretta, in Cheste
4 CONC r County, her home county after she came from Alsace, and after a short courtship they were married in April of 1728 in Berks County, his home county. He died 13 Sep 1794 in Heidelberg Township, Berks
4 CONC  County, Pennsylvania. He was buried in the German Reformed Church Burial Grounds, Reading, Pennsylvania, having been a devout member of the Reformed Church. The farm where he and Marguerite lived whe
4 CONC n they married was shown by a subsequent survey to consist of 78 acres. It was in the rich limestone region of the Lebanon Valley in what is called the Tulpehocken region of Pennsylvania, &#039;Tulpeh
4 CONC ocken&#039; being a Native American term for &#039;land of the turtles,&#039; and the name of the creek that supplies the territory with water. (The land so called takes in about 206,000 acres, roughl
4 CONC y 322 square miles.)

Children of Marguerite Simone and Johann Michael Bright:

