2 NOTE <p>Lauren Tabor <lmcrwls9@yahoo.com></p><p><p>7/5/14</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>to me</p></p><p><p>lmcrwls9 We are certainly related to each other Troy. John Augustus' first born child, John Mills Cox
3 CONC  was my great grandfather. There is a family Bible in Orlando, Fl. who has John A's children listed as John Mills, Robert H., William W., Ossie (a female), Eva and Ethel. I think Ossie is a nickname f
3 CONC or Cornellia which is found on some census records.</p><p><p>John A. was married to Frances Narcissus "Fannie" Lord and they had these 6 children together. She died in 1888 and he married Malissa in 1
3 CONC 891. Eva and Ethel were 13 and 15 and still living with him when he married Malissa.</p><p>One lady told me once that Eva's middle name was Amelia. I put Manning in my tree and most of the trees for h
3 CONC im list a John Andrew as one of his children, so I still wonder if Manning is right. I sure hope he is. I have a story to tell you about us being related to Jesse Jackson. Apparently, Manning or whoev
3 CONC er our 3rd great gf was, impregnated a black girl/woman in the early 1870's and she gave birth to a daughter, Ella Ruth Cox, who was Jesse's paternal grandmother. Am so anxious to hear from you again,
3 CONC  Laurie
