3 ROLE 40001:4870570:
1 NOTE When Marguerite/Margaret/Margareta/Margaretha Julianne Simone was born on March 21, 1708, in Pfeffelbach, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany (or in France - control of the area went back and forth), her fa
2 CONC ther, Jacob/Jacques, was 22, and her mother, Agnes, was 22. She married Johann/John Michael "Michael" Brecht in April 1728 in Heidelberg (now Schaefferstown), Lebanon County, Pennsylvania. They had te
2 CONC n children in 18 years. Michael met his future wife, Marguerita Simone/Simon, also shown as Margareta, Marguerite, and Margaretta, in Chester County, her home county after she came from Alsace, and af
2 CONC ter a short courtship they were married in April of 1728 in Berks County, his home county. He died 13 Sep 1784 in Heidelberg Township, Berks County, Pennsylvania. He was buried in the German Reformed 
2 CONC Church Burial Grounds, Reading, Pennsylvania, having been a devout member of the Reformed Church. The farm where he and Marguerite lived when they married was shown by a subsequent survey to consist o
2 CONC f 78 acres. It was in the rich limestone region of the Lebanon Valley in what is called the Tulpehocken region of Pennsylvania, 'Tulpehocken' being a Native American term for 'land of the turtles,' an
2 CONC d the name of the creek that supplies the territory with water. (The land so called takes in about 206,000 acres, roughly 322 square miles.)
She died on March 21, 1778, at the age of 70, and was burie
2 CONC d in the Trinity Lutheran Church Cemetery, Reading, Pennsylvania. 
Children of Marguerite Simone and Johann Michael Bright:

