1 NOTE Jacob BRECHT, b. April 13, 1729; d. 1802; m. Susannah/Susan RITTENHOUSE, 1 February 1750/51. He was born to . . . and  . . ..  on 13 Apr 1729 in Heidelberg Twp., Pennsylvania, and died in 1802 in Penn
2 CONC sylvania. Children of the marriage to Susannah: . . . ;  . . . ;  . . . . Jacob moved to Philadelphia in 1751. In 1770 he went into partnership with his brother-in-law, Christopher Pechin, shipping go
2 CONC ods to the South. During the American Revolution he raised a company of 90 men and was given a captain's commission. He was the first to leave the old homestead and was married in the German Reformed 
2 CONC Church of Philadelphia on 1 February 1751, to Susanna Rittenhouse, a near relative of the celebrated David Rittenhouse. 

see

