1 NOTE David Brecht was born 9 August 1740  in Lebanon Township in Pennsylvania to Marguerite Julianne Simone and Michael Brecht, the elder.  He married Mary Gail Grant in about 1769.  Children of this union
2 CONC :  See below. He supported his family as a miller and followed that trade in his own business for several years near Schaefferstown. He then moved to the Swatara Valley above the Blue Mountains in Ber
2 CONC ks County, about 20 miles north of Schaefferstown. His immediate area there became part of Pinegrove when it was organized in 1771. His name was written 'Brecht' until 1783. In 1784 he moved to Greenb
2 CONC riar County, Virginia. where he farmed until his death.

SAR Patriot Burial records list his burial as being in Charles Evans Cemetery in Reading, Pennsylvania, so he may have returned from Virginia a
2 CONC nd been in Berks County before his death. His will was written in Greenbriar County in Virginia.

His father, Michael Bright, the elder, emigrated from the Palatinate, Germany, in 1726, arriving in Pe
2 CONC nnsylvania at the age of 20 and settling near Schaefferstown. At that time there were but three counties in the Province of Pennsylvania, Philadelphia, Bucks and Chester. Schaefferstown was in Chester
2 CONC  County when the elder Michael Bright (then written as 'Brecht') arrived and was one of the oldest towns in the state. In 1729 Lancaster was established, and Schaefferstown was included with that coun
2 CONC ty, which later became Lebanon County.

His family
Mary Gail Grant (1744-1836)
Married 1770
Children

-Mary ("Polly") (1766-1844) m. Henry Ingle 1764-1822 of Phila. (had seven children)
-Michael (1771
2 CONC -1833) married Barbara Miller (ten children)
-David Grant (1775-1851) Moved to Botetourt Va. where he married Miss Graham in Fincastle, Va. in 1800. The same year he moved to Plattsburg, N.Y., by the 
2 CONC advice of DeWitt Clinton. He moved again in 1812 to Norwich, Chenango County, N.Y. In 1820 he moved to Madison, Ind., where he died. 
-Jesse W. (1773-1856) had a son, Jesse, who lived in Greenbriar Co
2 CONC ., Virginia
-Elizabeth 1781 m. _____  Moore, moved to Colorado Springs, Colorado (one child, Anna).
-George (1782-1873) born in Pinegrove Twp., later lived in Berks County, m. 1st Mary M. Neal (1787-1
2 CONC 827); rmoved with father to Greenbriar, Virginia, in 1785. Had 11 children with 1st wife, three children with 2nd wife, Ann Conell.
-Margaret (1780), m. Mr. Graham
see
Reading Times 11/21/1900
