1 NOTE Cumberland County History Book 974.83 W 721 by William Wagner lists the Stoner family. George was a farmer.
His family were members of St. Peter's Lutheran Church which was later founded in Newville. 
2 CONC George was one of the first settlers in this area.
the first settlers of Frankford Township. The maiden name of his wife, Catherine, is unknown,

To David Stoner Administrators release Vol 1 page 67-A
2 CONC pril 14th 1832
Whereas George Stoner late of Frankfort Township, died interstate (no will) the 28th day of September A.D. 1831 and whereas the said David Stoner was legallly appointed his administrato
2 CONC r of the said deceased on the 14th day of October 1831 and by amicable settlement between the Administrators said deceased estate his balance of $663.44 to be distributed according to the law among th
2 CONC e heirs of the said deceased.
