"Thomas StackhouseA, the son of John and perhaps his second wife, Ellen (__), was baptized 1 May 1601 in St. Alkelda's in Giggleswick. He died and was burie
2 CONC d in October 1686. Thomas married Anna (__). She was buried July 1690 in Giggleswick.[5]

Children of Thomas and Anna (__) Stackhouse (may be incomplete):[6]

i. Thomas Stackhouse1, d.y.

ii. John Sta
2 CONC ckhouse, was born 1633 in Giggleswick, W. Riding, Yorkshire.

iii. Thomas Stackhouse, Sr., twin, born 1635?? in Giggleswick, West Riding, Yorks, Eng. He died 1706 in Bucks Co, Penna.; m. 1682 Margery 
2 CONC HAYHURST; emigrated to Penna.; no children.

iv. Janet Stackhouse, born 1637 in Giggleswick, W. Riding, Yorkshire; bequeathed 1 shilling by her brother Thomas.

v. Ellen Stackhouse, twin was born 1639
2 CONC ?? and died after 1705, when she was named in her brother Thomas's will, to receive one shilling.

vi. William Stackhouse.

vii. Anna Stackhouse."

