===Children of John Stackhouse===

The Stackhouses of Bucks are descend
2 CONC ed from Thomas and John who came over prior to 1685.  

Thomas married
# Grace Heaton, daughter of Robert and Alice, of Middletown Meeting, 7 mo. 27, 1688;
# Ann, widow of Edward Mayos
# Dorothy, wido
2 CONC w of Zebulon Heston, Wrightstown. 

Thomas Stackhouse was the father of fourteen children and died 4 mo. 26, 1744. 

His brother John Stackhouse married Elizabeth Pearson or Pierson, 7  mo. 1702, and 
2 CONC had nine children.  She died 1743 and he, 1757, and both were buried at Middletown. 

The children of Thomas and John Stackhouse, in the first generation  intermarried with the families of Clark, Ston
2 CONC e, Wilson, Longshore,  Copeland, Gilbert, Watson, Plumley, Cary, Haring, Janney, Mitchell,  Stephenson, Tomlinson and others and their descendants are almost legion.  The Baileys of Buckingham, are de
2 CONC scended from Jacob, second, son of Thomas  Stackhouse, and Ann Mayos, born 8 mo. 25, 1713, married 3 mo. 25, 1742.  Hannah Watson, daughter of Amos and Mary (Hillborn) Watson, had four  children.
